## Journal Project App Registry

This project uses a single-spa micro-frontend architecture with these registered apps:

| App Name (single-spa) | Package Name | Dev Port | Entry | Route |
|------------------------|-------------|----------|-------|-------|
| `@cnic/main` | `@cnic/main` | 9100 | `http://localhost:9100/app.js` | `/j` (always active) |
| `@journal/submit` | `@journal/submit` | 9110 | `http://localhost:9110/app.js` | `/j/:id/my/submit` |
| `@journal/review` | `@journal/review` | 9120 | `http://localhost:9120/app.js` | `/j/:id/my/review` & `/j/:id/quick-review` |
| `@journal/edit` | `@journal/edit` | 9130 | `http://localhost:9130/app.js` | `/j/:id/my/edit` |
| `@journal/publish` | `@journal/publish` | 9140 | `http://localhost:9140/app.js` | `/j/:id/my/publish` |
| `@journal/manage` | `@journal/manage` | 9150 | `http://localhost:9150/app.js` | `/j/:id/my/manage` |
| `@cnic/root-config` | `@cnic/root-config` | 9000 | `http://localhost:9000/cnic-root-config.js` | (root) |

**Note:** The root-config's local import map uses `@cnic/*` aliases for some apps (e.g., `@cnic/submit` maps to port 9110). When setting overrides, use the **single-spa app name** from the layout definition (`@journal/*` for child apps, `@cnic/main` for the main app).

### Override example for developing @journal/edit locally:

```
override_app { action: "set", appName: "@journal/edit", url: "http://localhost:9130/app.js" }
```

